The user is saying that when they first opened the app, the "Open" button wasn't visible at all, and it only appeared after the icons were loaded. Let me look at the code to understand why.

The issue is in the `HeaderOpenButton` component — it returns `null` when `apps.length === 0`:

```tsx
if (apps.length === 0) {
    return null;
}
```

The apps are loaded asynchronously via `native.apps.getInstalled()`. While they're loading, `apps` is an empty array, so the button is hidden entirely. Once the IPC call resolves (which includes icon extraction via PlistBuddy + sips for each app — that's 5+ sequential subprocess calls), the button appears.


The solution is to render the button immediately in a loading state rather than hiding it completely, then fill in the icons as they load. The button's visibility shouldn't be tied to whether the apps data has arrived yet.

